"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-08-02-olympian-gets-engaged-teammate-just-moments-winning-gold-21351776\", \"text\": \"Parisis both the host of theOlympicsand the city of love and this was certainly the case for two Chinese athletes on Friday.  Chinawon gold in the badminton mixed doubles final, with Huang Yaqiong and Zheng Siwei triumphing over Kim Won-ho and Jeong Na-eun of South Korea.  Huang is a highly-decorated athlete having previously won silver in Tokyo as well as three world championships.  Follow\\u00a0Metro.co.uk's live blog for updates from the Paris 2024 Olympics  And she will be leaving the French capital with not just a gold medal but also a diamond ring after her boyfriend and fellow Olympian proposed following the medal ceremony.  Liu Yuchen, who competes in the badminton men's doubles, got on one knee and asked for Huang's hand to which she said yes.  The crowd cheered on the happy couple, in what is actually the third marriage proposal of these Paris Olympics.  The boyfriends of French sailors\\u00a0Sarah Steyaert and Charline Picon\\u00a0proposed to the pair after they won bronze in the skiff sailing. Both said yes.  \\\"I\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ll love you forever! Will you marry me?\\\"\\\"Yes! I do!\\\"OMG!!! Romance at the Olympics!!!\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008f\\u00e2\\u009d\\u00a4\\u00ef\\u00b8\\u008fHuang Yaqiong just had her \\\"dream come true\\\", winning a badminton mixed doubles gold medal\\u00f0\\u009f\\u00a5\\u0087with her teammate Zheng SiweiThen her boyfriend Liu Yuchen proposed! \\u00f0\\u009f\\u008e\\u0089\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008e\\u0089\\u00f0\\u009f\\u008e\\u0089pic.twitter.com/JxMIipF7ij  Unlike his now-fiancee however, Liu will not be winning a medal himself after he and partner Ou Xuanyi were knocked out at the group stage, though China can still win the men's doubles through a different pair.  The Chinese have a big lead in the medal table as it stands, with 13 golds and 27 medals total.  For more stories like this,check our sport page.  Follow Metro Sport for the latest news onFacebook,TwitterandInstagram.  ArrowMORE:'Surreal!' - Team GB star reacts after winning gold 12 years after his father did in same event  ArrowMORE:Lin Yu-ting becomes second Olympic boxer to win after failed gender test  ArrowMORE:Angela Carini issues apology to Imane Khelif after Olympic boxing controversy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy  Punchy analysis, transfer talk and more from Metro's football experts, sent straight to your inbox every week.  Let us know which team you support.Close  This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and theGoogle Privacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply. Your information will be used in line with ourPrivacy Policy\"}"